### 3. Security Implementation

To safeguard system integrity and secure business intelligence, we will apply industry-standard backend security layers:

| Vulnerability / Risk | Mitigation Strategy | Implementation Tool |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Plaintext Password Leaks** | Hash passwords at rest using adaptive hashing algorithms. | `bcrypt` (10 salt rounds) |
| **Session Hijacking / CSRF** | Issue signed HTTP-only, secure cookies with short expiration windows. | `jsonwebtoken` (JWT) cookie storage |
| **Unauthorized Role Access** | Check user roles in middleware before letting requests reach controller logic. | Custom express role verification helper |
| **SQL/NoSQL Injections** | Use schemas with strict casting. Sanitize incoming payload fields. | Mongoose Models + `express-validator` |
| **DoS / Rate Limit Attacks** | Limit query counts on open auth/login routes. | `express-rate-limit` |
| **Cross-Origin / Header Risks** | Establish secure request validation and block insecure HTTP protocols. | `helmet` + configured `cors` middleware |

